                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Dynamic Routing and API Integration</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Landing Proxiflare leverages ExpressJS to create dynamic routes for each generated landing page. When a page is created, it automatically sends an API call to Proxyflare to configure DNS and proxy settings, pointing to the specific subpath in Landing Proxiflare (e.g., /page/my-landing).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Self-Hosting Configuration</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">To self-host Landing Proxiflare, you'll need to configure the following environment variables:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">MONGODB_URI</code>: Your MongoDB connection string</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">DBNAME</code>: Set to "landing_proxyflare"</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">PROXYFLARE_URL</code>: The public URL of your Proxyflare instance</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">PROXYFLARE_APIKEY</code>: Your Proxyflare API key</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">PROXYFLARE_PROXY_HOST_DEFAULT</code>: Your server's static IP address</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">PROXYFLARE_PROXY_PORT_DEFAULT</code>: The exposed Docker port for the Landing proxyflare instance</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">AUTH_USER</code>: Admin username (default: admin)</li>
                    <li><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">AUTH_PASSWORD</code>: Admin password (default: admin)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Ensure these variables are properly set to enable seamless integration between Landing Proxiflare and Proxyflare.</p>
